      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC05b333482b23100589efb93796bc81c4"></a>Removing the throttle twistgrip
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6342"> </a>Remove the counterweight plug (1) from the handlebar.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_016803263.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6347"> </a>Slightly pull back the rubber sleeve (2) protecting the throttle control cables.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_016903264.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6352"> </a>Undo the screws (3) of the throttle grip (4) and open the control.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_017003265.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6357"> </a>Remove the throttle control cables (5) by disengaging pawls (6) from their seats.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6359"> </a>Remove the throttle twistgrip (4) from the handlebar.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_017103266.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6364"> </a>To replace the throttle grip cables, it is necessary to remove them from the throttle body.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e6367"> </a>Spare throttle cables are supplied complete with adjusters.
         </div>
      </div>
